					<div class="form-group my-3 row justify-content-center">
						<h4 class = "py-1 col col-12">Please read the rules</h4>
						<div class = "py-1 col col-12">
							<div class="card rounded my-3">
								<ul class="list-group list-group-flush mt-0">
									<li class="list-group-item p-0  text-center mt-0">
										<a class="m-3 pink-btn btn btn-primary mb-2 join-league-btn" href="#readBeforePlaying" data-toggle="collapse" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseExample">
											<h5 class = "mb-0">Read them here</h5>
										</a>

										<div class="text-left collapse card-body pre-scrollable p-1" id="readBeforePlaying">

											<hr>
	                    <h4 class="card-title text-center">Condensed version</h4>
	                    <ul class="card-text pl-3">
	                      <li>Be nice</li>
	                      <li>Show up to games you sign up for!</li>
	                      <li>Join and use the Discord</li>
	                      <li>Report any violations or bad behaviour to the Wecasual team<</li>
	                      <li>Failing to abide by the rules can result in the removal of Wecasual</li>
	                      <li>If you have questions or concerns email: <a href="mailto:robert@wecasual.gg">robert@wecasual.gg</a></span><span >&nbsp;or dm Robert on discord</li>
	                    </ul>
	                    <hr>
	                    <h4 class="card-title text-center">Full version</h4>
	                    <p>Wecasual has a mission to ELIMINATE ALL TOXIC BEHAVIOUR
	                      FROM ESPORT GAMES THROUGH ORGANIZED, FRIENDLY, AND WELCOMING PLAY. The following rules are designed to allow Wecasual to maintain a positive, and welcoming community. </p>

	                    <h4 class="card-title mt-2">Registration Rules</h4>
	                    <ul class="card-text pl-3">
	                      <li>To participate in Wecasual players must be under 4000 solo MMR</li>
	                      <ul>
	                        <li>Exceptions will be made on a case-by-case basis, contact <a href="mailto:robert@wecasual.gg">robert@wecasual.gg</a></li>
	                        <li>MMR must be publicly visible on your Dota 2 account in-client and on Dotabuff/OpenDota</li>
	                        <li>Party MMR will not be taken into account</li>
	                        <li>If you are not calibrated you can’t be playing in very high skill games (Dotabuff and OpenDota will be referenced)</li>
	                      </ul>
	                      <li>Each player may only register one account with Wecasual</li>
	                      <li>Players are not allowed to share accounts with any other players</li>
	                      <li>There is no registration cut off date</li>
	                    </ul>
	                    <h4 class="card-title mt-2">Player Rules</h4>
	                    <ul class="card-text pl-3">
	                      <li>While in Wecasual players must stay below the MMR cap (Exceptions will be made on a case-by-case basis)</li>
	                      <li>Wecasual reserves the right to remove a player from the community due to skill level disparity</li>
	                      <ul>
	                        <li>This manner of player removal is for play balancing reasons</li>
	                      </ul>
	                    </ul>
	                    <h4 class="card-title mt-2">Conduct</h4>
	                    <ul class="card-text pl-3">
	                      <li>All community members must act in a respectful manner while in the Wecasul community</li>
	                      <ul>
	                        <li>This includes on the Wecasual Discord, Wecasual Website, and any Wecasual games</li>
	                      </ul>
	                      <li>No verbal attacks or rude remarks to any other person</li>
	                      <li>No harassment of any Wecasual community members</li>
	                      <li>No spam</li>
	                      <li>No sharing or posting of offensive or NSFW content anywhere in the Wecasual community space</li>
	                    </ul>
	                    <h4 class="card-title mt-2">League Rules</h4>
	                    <ul class="card-text pl-3">
	                      <li>The league is continuous and there are no playoffs or end to a ‘season’</li>
	                      <li>Games are best of 1 (Unless otherwise specified)</li>
	                      <li>Lobbies will be hosted by Wecasual or official lobby hosters</li>
	                      <li>If you are unable to attend a game you signed up for please contact a Wecasual team member</li>
	                      <li>You must give at least 48 hours notice of your absence, continued late notice will result in disciplinary action</li>
	                      <li>Any game with insufficient sign ups 24 hours before game time will be cancelled</li>
	                    </ul>
	                    <h4 class="card-title mt-2">Lobbies and In-Game Rules</h4>
	                    <ul class="card-text pl-3">
	                      <li>All players should be in lobby 5 minutes prior to the official start time</li>
	                      <li>Pauses are permitted for any reasonable issues</li>
	                      <ul>
	                        <li>This includes: lag and packet loss, a disconnect, urgent bathroom break, someone at the door, etc. Please use your best judgement when it comes to pauses</li>
	                        <li>If there is an issue with pausing in-game contact a Wecasual team member via email or on Discord</li>
	                      </ul>
	                      <li>No all chat of any variations of “gg” outside of forfeiting the match</li>
	                      <ul>
	                        <li>Any accidental all chat of “gg” without the intention of forfeiting should be immediately followed by all chat informing the opposing team that they will not be forfeiting</li>
	                        <li>Any fake “gg” calls with be result in a warning and then a forfeit</li>
	                      </ul>
	                      <li>Positive and friendly all chat is permitted</li>
	                      <li>Any negative (even with playful or good intentions) will not be permitted</li>
	                      <li>All players must use voice chat in the Wecasual Discord to communicate with their team</li>
	                    </ul>
	                    <h4 class="card-title mt-2">Reporting</h4>
	                    <ul class="card-text pl-3">
	                      <li>Players may report any violations of the Wecasual rules</li>
	                      <li>All and any reports can be sent to<a href="mailto:robert@wecasual.gg">robert@wecasual.gg</a> or to Robert on Discord</li>
	                      <li>Please include the match ID, team names, and player names of those involved</li>
	                      <li>It is recommended to include other evidence such as screenshots or recordings as well as having consensus among the players in the match that the rules were broken</li>
	                    </ul>
	                    <h4 class="card-title mt-2">Disciplinary Actions </h4>
	                    <ul class="card-text pl-3">
	                      <li>The first two violations of the rules will result in warnings</li>
	                      <li>The third violation of the rules will result in a removal from Wecasual</li>
	                      <li>Any Wecasual team member reserves the right to remove any player from the league with no prior warnings under extreme circumstances</li>
	                    </ul>



										</div>
									</li>
								</ul>
							</div>
							<label class="form-check-label">
								<input type="checkbox" name="rules" class="form-check-input">
								By checking this box I understand and agree to the rules of Wecasual.
							</label>
						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="form-group my-3 row justify-content-center">
						<h4 class = "py-1 col col-12">Code of Conduct</h4>
						<div class = "py-1 col col-12">
							<div class="mb-3">
								<p>Wecasual is about fun and community above all else. We are not a competitive community.</p>
							</div>
							<label class="form-check-label">
								<input type="checkbox" name="conduct" class="form-check-input">
								By checking this box I understand the above statement.
							</label>
						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="form-group text-center">
						<input type="submit" value="Sign up" class = "btn btn-secondary btn-lg btn-block">
					</div>
				</form>
			</div>
		</div>
